{"updated_at": {"date": {"d": "03", "m": "04", "Y": "2026"}, "time": {"H": "14", "M": "34", "S": "39"}}, "news": [{"title": "Panchkula drops plan to shift illegal Gandhi Colony for now", "para": "Panchkula administration has postponed plans to relocate the illegal Gandhi Colony, a slum near Mata Mansa Devi Mandir, citing recent festivals. Despite surveys and land earmarking, the move, aimed at beautifying temple premises, faces delays, with sources suggesting upcoming municipal elections as a factor. Insanitary conditions persist, impacting devotees and residents.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/infrastructure/panchkula-drops-plan-to-shift-illegal-gandhi-colony-for-now/129993686?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-216214/129993686.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "infrastructure"}, {"title": "Belagavi: Probe ordered into alleged violations at 10-storey building near BCC office", "para": "Belagavi City Commissioner Karthik K has ordered an investigation into a 10-storey building in Shivaji Nagar. The probe will examine suspected building violations and the issuance of property identification numbers. Concerns exist about potential non-compliance with regulations and approvals. The commissioner stated appropriate action will follow the findings.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/infrastructure/investigation-launched-into-building-code-violations-at-belagavis-controversial-10-storey-construction/129993673?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-44012/129993673.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "infrastructure"}, {"title": "Ludhiana civic body orders survey of illegal hotels built after 2021", "para": "Ludhiana's Municipal Corporation is surveying hotels built after 2021 following complaints of illegal construction and violations of building bylaws.  A committee has been formed to investigate these unauthorized establishments, with a focus on issues like inadequate parking causing traffic congestion.  Officials are directed to submit detailed reports for necessary action.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/hospitality/ludhiana-cracks-down-on-illegal-hotels-comprehensive-survey-ordered/129993654?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-64798/129993654.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "hospitality"}]}